modules.description: This module defines a partition entry in a GPT (GUID Partition Table) with fields for type, partition GUIDs, start and end LBA addresses, attributes, and name. It provides functions to construct a partition with validation, check if a partition is unused, and serialize/deserialize partitions to and from binary buffers. It is used to manage individual partition entries when reading or writing GPT data structures on disk.

This module implements operations for creating, parsing, and serializing GPT (GUID Partition Table) structures. It works with a structured type representing GPT headers and partition entries, including validation, checksum handling, and alignment with disk geometry. It is used to generate valid GPT data for disk imaging, parse GPT headers and partition tables from raw disk data, and write GPT structures to disk images or devices.
